    "en": {
      "title": "At least 90 percent of the buses will run tomorrow",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Gemunu Wijeratne, President of Ceylon Private Bus Owners Association, says that despite the problems, at least 90 percent of the buses will be run tomorrow to meet the transportation needs of school children.",
        "The Ministry of Education has decided to implement the limited school activities due to the fuel crisis from tomorrow on all five days of the week.",
        "He also said that there are problems in obtaining fuel from some depots and that this problem is acute in some places in the southern province."
      ],
